cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.MA, cs.SI, cs.DS 

The paper deals with resource sharing among multiple devices owned by different mobile users, which involves distributed computing and networking. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also involves communication and networking, which makes cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) another likely category. The use of auctions and optimization algorithms suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the numerical experiments and the fair allocation of resources suggest that the paper could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
